Spies x2     </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">  <br>
Strategy: You start Pippin so you can did 3-4, usually 3. So that you can start the Pony to pull Aragorn. Use skirmish cancellers, until your fellowship is set up. I am Just plain tired of the Legolas and Arwen start so I thought I try it this way, so I will automatically have Boromir out. Use PATHS stop swarms, use with ARV, or just kill minions. Filbert Bolger is awesome at site 9 to cancel fierce skirmishes. This deck is very good at double moving, and usually wins by winning the race to site 9. This deck usually moves: 1-3, 3-4, 4-6, 6-8, 8-9. <br>
<br>
However the shadow site can also win if you are behind in the race you can still win with the shadow. If you have small twilight choke/ranger fellowships in your area then you can use the Moria, but if you see alot of big fellowships then you can use the Uruks to destroy them. Both shadow sides are very strong and can be used in either environment, depending on your preference. <br>
<br>
D-mail me if you have any questions <br>
<br>
Thanks!  <br>
